    "longBusinessSummary": "Saudi Industrial Export Company provides supply chain and trade solutions in the Middle East and African regions. The company engages in the wholesale of lubricating oils and refined petroleum products, cement, plaster and the like, plastic materials, rubber and synthetic fibers; and storage in ports. It offers payment alternatives and financing solutions to fund and expand operations; commodity exchange solutions and warehouse management systems; and commercial insurance protection services. It also provides physical movement of goods services for import and export, including drayage to and from ports; negotiated trucking, air, and containership contracted rates; coverage of all lanes and capacity requirements; value-added services, packaging, kitting, and processing; collateral management agreements; and chartering services/bulk logistics. In addition, the company offers integrated information flow solutions, including internal market research data mine and IQ International capabilities; SaaS ecommerce platform for trading, product cataloging, vendor profiles, and routing guide compliance; configures, manages, and expands B2B storefronts; control tower visibility across entire supply chain; transactions across all currencies; and bid options on required services. Saudi Industrial Export Company was incorporated in 1990 and is headquartered in Riyadh, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.",
